Template: debian-installer/iso-scan/title
Type: text
#  Main menu item
_Description: Scan hard drives for an installer ISO

Template: iso-scan/progress_title
Type: text
_Description: Searching drives for an installer ISO

Template: iso-scan/progress_pass1
Type: text
_Description: Mounting ${DRIVE} ...

Template: iso-scan/progress_pass2
Type: text
_Description: Scanning ${DRIVE} ...

Template: iso-scan/progress_pass2_dir
Type: text
_Description: Scanning ${DRIVE} (in ${DIRECTORY}) ...

Template: iso-scan/no-isos
Type: text
_Description: Failed to find an installer ISO
 No installer ISO was found on any of the ${NUM_FILESYSTEMS} file systems(s)
 scanned. Either the ISO is not present, or it has the wrong filename, or
 the file system it is on cannot be mounted.

Template: iso-scan/corrupt-isos
Type: test
_Description: Failed to find an installer ISO
 Of ${ISO_COUNT} ISO image(s) found, only ${ISO_MOUNT_COUNT} could not be
 mounted, and an installer ISO was not found. Perhaps the ISO you
 downloaded is corrupt?

Template: iso-scan/bad-isos
Type: text
_Description: Found no installer ISOs
 ${ISO_COUNT} ISO image(s) were found, but none were valid installer ISOs.
